(404, 1, '2016-03-22 13:05:26', '2016-03-22 13:05:26', '&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Dear online traders,</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Dear webshop owners,</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">There is a new legislation rule regarding online shopping.The European commission has made “a step forward” for the European citizens who shop and sell online.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">From 15 February 2016 there is a functioning online platform(ODR - Online Dispute Resolution) which is intended to be used by customers and traders who have chosen the Internet as a marketplace. It aims to simplify and make the process of solving cross-border disputes inside the European Union faster,cheaper and more efficient. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">From now on, you as an online trader are obliged to:</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n<h3><span style="color: #000000;"><b><b>provide a link* to the ODR platform and your own email address on your website</b></b></span></h3>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="color: #000000;"><b>provide a link* to the ODR platform and your own email address on commercial offers sent via email</b></span></li>\r\n	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="color: #000000;"><b>provide the same information in the general terms and conditions applicable to online sales and service contracts.</b></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #0000ff;"><b>*https://webgate.ec.europa.eu/odr/main/?event=main.home.show</b></span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The ODR is an improvement to the already existing ADR (Alternative Dispute Resolution). For those of you who are not aware of </span><a style="color: #000000;" href="http://ec.europa.eu/consumers/solving_consumer_disputes/docs/adr-odr_for_web.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">ADR and ODR</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, we give a short description:</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">“Alternative dispute resolution (ADR) helps consumers resolve disputes with traders when they have a problem with a product or service that they bought e.g. when a trader refuses to repair a product or to make a refund to which a consumer is entitled.</span></i></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">ADR entities are out-of-court (non-judicial) entities. They involve a neutral party (e.g. a conciliator, mediator, arbitrator, ombudsman, complaints board etc.) who proposes or imposes a solution or brings the parties together to help them find a solution.</span></i></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Some of these entities operate fully online and are called online dispute resolution (ODR) entities. This can help solve disputes with online purchases, when the consumer and the trader are located far from each other.</span></i></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">ADR and ODR are usually </span></i><b><i>low-cost, simple and fast procedures</i></b><i><span style="font-weight: 400;"> and are therefore beneficial to both consumers and traders, who can avoid court costs and procedures. ADR and ODR are not internal customer complaint services ran by traders.”</span></i></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">- European Commission Memo, Brussels, 12 March 2013</span></i></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">The online version has been working a few days already and it aims to make the whole procedure easier,faster, cheaper and more efficient for both consumers and traders.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">The ODR platform is interactive, working in the EU''s 23 official languages , specifically developed to assist people who have a complaint about products or services they have purchased online.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">When using the ODR platform consumers or traders complete an online form and decide which ADR entity shall be competent to settle their dispute from a </span><a style="color: #000000;" href="https://webgate.ec.europa.eu/odr/main/?event=main.adr.show"><span style="font-weight: 400;">list</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> where everything about the registered entities is described in details such as sector of competence, procedure and contact information.</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Afterwards, the ADR entity has 90 days to handle the case and come up with a decision.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">For more information on how it works you can visit the </span></i><a style="color: #000000;" href="http://ec.europa.eu/consumers/solving_consumer_disputes/non-judicial_redress/adr-odr/index_en.htm"><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">ODR website</span></i></a><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span></i></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">The new platform is beneficial both for consumers and traders since they will be able to solve contractual disputes on- or offline, locally or cross-border through out-of-court entities which means that it will be faster and cheaper for both sides.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">This could be a real step forward because businesses will be provided with new opportunities and there will be an economic growth.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'The new link you need to put on your webshop', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '200-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-03-22 13:05:26', '2016-03-22 13:05:26', '', 200, 'http://wearecrunch.net/newsite/2016/03/22/200-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(405, 1, '2016-03-22 13:06:33', '2016-03-22 13:06:33', '&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Dear webshop owners,</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">There is a new legislation rule regarding online shopping.The European commission has made “a step forward” for the European citizens who shop and sell online.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">From 15 February 2016 there is a functioning online platform(ODR - Online Dispute Resolution) which is intended to be used by customers and traders who have chosen the Internet as a marketplace. It aims to simplify and make the process of solving cross-border disputes inside the European Union faster,cheaper and more efficient. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">From now on, you as an online trader are obliged to:</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n<h3><span style="color: #000000;"><b><b>provide a link* to the ODR platform and your own email address on your website</b></b></span></h3>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="color: #000000;"><b>provide a link* to the ODR platform and your own email address on commercial offers sent via email</b></span></li>\r\n	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="color: #000000;"><b>provide the same information in the general terms and conditions applicable to online sales and service contracts.</b></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #0000ff;"><b>*https://webgate.ec.europa.eu/odr/main/?event=main.home.show</b></span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The ODR is an improvement to the already existing ADR (Alternative Dispute Resolution). For those of you who are not aware of </span><a style="color: #000000;" href="http://ec.europa.eu/consumers/solving_consumer_disputes/docs/adr-odr_for_web.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">ADR and ODR</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, we give a short description:</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">“Alternative dispute resolution (ADR) helps consumers resolve disputes with traders when they have a problem with a product or service that they bought e.g. when a trader refuses to repair a product or to make a refund to which a consumer is entitled.</span></i></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">ADR entities are out-of-court (non-judicial) entities. They involve a neutral party (e.g. a conciliator, mediator, arbitrator, ombudsman, complaints board etc.) who proposes or imposes a solution or brings the parties together to help them find a solution.</span></i></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Some of these entities operate fully online and are called online dispute resolution (ODR) entities. This can help solve disputes with online purchases, when the consumer and the trader are located far from each other.</span></i></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">ADR and ODR are usually </span></i><b><i>low-cost, simple and fast procedures</i></b><i><span style="font-weight: 400;"> and are therefore beneficial to both consumers and traders, who can avoid court costs and procedures. ADR and ODR are not internal customer complaint services ran by traders.”</span></i></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">- European Commission Memo, Brussels, 12 March 2013</span></i></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">The online version has been working a few days already and it aims to make the whole procedure easier,faster, cheaper and more efficient for both consumers and traders.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">The ODR platform is interactive, working in the EU''s 23 official languages , specifically developed to assist people who have a complaint about products or services they have purchased online.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">When using the ODR platform consumers or traders complete an online form and decide which ADR entity shall be competent to settle their dispute from a </span><a style="color: #000000;" href="https://webgate.ec.europa.eu/odr/main/?event=main.adr.show"><span style="font-weight: 400;">list</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> where everything about the registered entities is described in details such as sector of competence, procedure and contact information.</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Afterwards, the ADR entity has 90 days to handle the case and come up with a decision.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">For more information on how it works you can visit the </span></i><a style="color: #000000;" href="http://ec.europa.eu/consumers/solving_consumer_disputes/non-judicial_redress/adr-odr/index_en.htm"><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">ODR website</span></i></a><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span></i></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">The new platform is beneficial both for consumers and traders since they will be able to solve contractual disputes on- or offline, locally or cross-border through out-of-court entities which means that it will be faster and cheaper for both sides.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">This could be a real step forward because businesses will be provided with new opportunities and there will be an economic growth.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'The new link you need to put on your webshop', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '200-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-03-22 13:06:33', '2016-03-22 13:06:33', '', 200, 'http://wearecrunch.net/newsite/2016/03/22/200-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(406, 1, '2016-04-13 09:51:23', '2016-04-13 09:51:23', '<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">In the contemporary world of computers and smartphones, a company website is a must-have. It is your primary tool for online marketing so it gives you the opportunity to communicate easily with your customers. However, "to improve is to change, to perfect is to change often." This is also valid for your website. But how would you know if your website is in urgent need of a redesign?</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Below we''ve listed the main signs that will help you find out.</span>\n\n<strong><span style="color: #000000;">It''s not mobile friendly</span></strong>\n\n<span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">As we said in the beginning mobile devices have taken a tremendous part of our everyday life. </span><a style="color: #000000;" href="http://www.emarketer.com/Article/Over-2-Million-Daily-Mobile-Web-Users-Denmark/1010984"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">According to a research</span> </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">over 2 million Danes are browsing on their mobile devices daily which means that if you are interested in online marketing you should have in mind the huge impact of the smartphones in our hands.</span></span>\n\n<span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you are not yet convinced that you should make your website responsive, check these </span><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><a style="color: #000000; text-decoration: underline;" href="https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/20140429232119-1981105-top-10-reasons-your-business-website-should-be-mobile-friendly">10 reasons from Keith Marlow</a>.</span></span></span>\n\n<strong><span style="color: #000000;">It''s not driving the same traffic as before</span></strong>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">One of the worst scenarios is when you are not getting the traffic you had expected. This means that either your marketing strategy is not appropriate or your website is not good enough to attract the attention of potential clients and make the users happy.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">If you face this kind of problem, it is time to redesign your website. You can improve your content with more interesting and useful articles or blog posts, include more images (because people prefer visuals rather than text) and also add some interactions on the website.</span>\n\n<strong><span style="color: #000000;">It''s not up-to-date</span></strong>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">The world of technology is one of the (if not THE) fastest changing industries. Which means that in just a few years or less some pretty cool stuff from today can be so old that no one remembers them . Keeping your website updated with the newest features and design trends is a guarantee for online marketing success. What''s more, the new technologies are made for better user experience so your outcome will be a satisfied customer.</span>\n\n<strong><span style="color: #000000;">It''s not easy to use</span></strong>\n\n<span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">If it happens that you are the one in charge of uploading content on your website, you might know that it could be hard for you to do it. But why is that? When today you have all the</span><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a style="color: #000000;" href="http://www.top10bestwebsitebuilders.com/WebsiteBuilders-Comparison?kw=professional%20web%20sites&amp;c=71889224917&amp;t=search&amp;p=&amp;m=p&amp;adpos=1t1&amp;dev=c&amp;devmod=&amp;mobval=0&amp;network=g&amp;campaignid=134707237&amp;adgroupid=7825402237&amp;targetid=kwd-101125489&amp;interest=&amp;physical=1005010&amp;feedid=&amp;a=2024&amp;ts=c&amp;topic=&amp;gclid=CjwKEAiArdG1BRCLvs_q-IObwxMSJACXbLtzHAhO0zlxY7-NHQi7FMDOdeokxJdbvndgT7fpKgHtMBoC6HXw_wcB"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> necessary tools to simplify the publishing process even if you are not a professional Web Designer. </span></a></span></span>\n\n<span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The other side of not good usability is that your </span><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a style="color: #000000;" href="http://usabilitygeek.com/10-characteristics-bad-user-experience/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">user experience will be very bad</span></a></span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> and people will not be happy with what you give them online. Again why making it hard for your business to flourish when technology gives you the possibilities to rise and shine?</span></span>\n\n<strong><span style="color: #000000;">It''s not working properly</span></strong>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Oh, no... We all hate this, don''t we?  But sometimes when your website has not been updated recently, some of the features might stop working.And the visitors will be quite disappointed with that so you won''t get the results you''ve expected.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">This is why it is extremely important to check occasionally for the newest versions and update when possible. As George Bernard Shaw said:</span>\n\n<span style="color: #000000;"><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">"Progress is impossible without change." </span></i></span>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Furthermore, don''t forget the increasing impact of </span><a style="color: #000000;" href="https://wearecrunchblog.wordpress.com/2016/02/04/6-things-you-should-do-when-promoting-your-business-in-social-media/"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">social media marketing</span> </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">and try to implement social buttons on visible places on your website.</span></span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Last but not least, redesigning your website can be an amazing marketing strategy to win business over your competitors.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Let us know if there is any way we can help you!</span>', 'Do you need to redesign your business website now?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '259-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-04-13 09:51:23', '2016-04-13 09:51:23', '', 259, 'http://wearecrunch.net/newsite/2016/03/22/259-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
