hing a good reputation online, gives you the opportunity to build better customer relationships and consequently attract new and bigger clients.</span> </span>', 'Why being present on the Internet is so important for your business?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '460-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-04-13 09:43:48', '2016-04-13 09:43:48', '', 460, 'http://wearecrunch.net/newsite/2016/04/13/460-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(466, 1, '2016-04-13 09:44:28', '2016-04-13 09:44:28', '<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">If you are one of the people who still wonder if they should spend time and money on online marketing, we advise you to continue reading. It is becoming more and more popular for any kind and size of businesses to show up online. But you don’t have the extra budget to spend this year on something that you are not sure is going to work for you? Well, if you need some reasons to convince you, here are ours: </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><strong>An easy and fast way to reach more people </strong></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you are reading this, it means that you are one of the</span><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a style="color: #000000;" href="http://www.statista.com/statistics/273018/number-of-internet-users-worldwide/"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> 3,17 billion Internet users</span></a></span><span style="font-weight: 400;">. A huge number, isn’t it?  Of course, you won’t reach all of them but for sure you will expand your reach. Whether you are trying to reach youngsters or middle-aged, even our grandparents have access to the Web these days. </span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;">Being visible online in the world of constant browsing can be crucial for your business. With your own website or blog, you will be able to show the World your products/services in a modern way and expand your reach.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;">Social media is also a huge part of our everyday life. It gives you the opportunity to connect to and communicate with your customers and present yourself as a professional in your area of work.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><strong>Cost effective </strong></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;">The budget is one of the most important parts of your business plan. When deciding whether or not to show up on the Internet, you might think that it could influence your budget in a negative way but consider this - the long term investment that you are making getting a company website will pay you back faster than you’ve imagined.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;">There are also quite a few things you can do to promote our business online for free. For example, getting a Facebook or LinkedIn company page or sharing thoughts and pictures on twitter and Instagram. You can read more about your social media marketing opportunities here: (link to the other blog post)</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><strong>Additional advertising and sales tool</strong></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">In the virtual world, the size of your company does not really matter. With a good online marketing strategy, you can out rank in Google big international competitors. In fact, there are more small businesses that are still invisible online, so this might be a huge benefit for you to go ahead of the others and give your customers more. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Consider also using social media to display for free your products or services. As </span><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a style="color: #000000; text-decoration: underline;" href="http://www.hubspot.com/company/management/brian-halligan"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Brian Halligan</span></a></span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> said</span><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">:” To be successful and grow your business and revenues, you must match the way you market your products with the way your prospects learn about and shop for your products.”</span></i></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><strong>Bigger impact </strong></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">All good managers know that if you are following the latest trends, you are highly competitive and people are more likely to ask for your products or services. </span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="color: #000000;">Expanding your reach and establishing a good reputation online, gives you the opportunity to build better customer relationships and consequently attract new and bigger clients.</span> </span>', 'Why being present on the Internet is so important for your business?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '460-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-04-13 09:44:28', '2016-04-13 09:44:28', '', 460, 'http://wearecrunch.net/newsite/2016/04/13/460-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(467, 1, '2016-04-13 09:52:13', '2016-04-13 09:52:13', '<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">In the contemporary world of computers and smartphones, a company website is a must-have. It is your primary tool for online marketing so it gives you the opportunity to communicate easily with your customers. However, "to improve is to change, to perfect is to change often." This is also valid for your website. But how would you know if your website is in urgent need of a redesign?</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Below we''ve listed the main signs that will help you find out.</span>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style="color: #000000;">It''s not mobile friendly</span></strong>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">As we said in the beginning mobile devices have taken a tremendous part of our everyday life. </span><a style="color: #000000;" href="http://www.emarketer.com/Article/Over-2-Million-Daily-Mobile-Web-Users-Denmark/1010984"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">According to a research</span> </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">over 2 million Danes are browsing on their mobile devices daily which means that if you are interested in online marketing you should have in mind the huge impact of the smartphones in our hands.</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you are not yet convinced that you should make your website responsive, check these </span><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><a style="color: #000000; text-decoration: underline;" href="https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/20140429232119-1981105-top-10-reasons-your-business-website-should-be-mobile-friendly">10 reasons from Keith Marlow</a>.</span></span></span>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style="color: #000000;">It''s not driving the same traffic as before</span></strong>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">One of the worst scenarios is when you are not getting the traffic you had expected. This means that either your marketing strategy is not appropriate or your website is not good enough to attract the attention of potential clients and make the users happy.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">If you face this kind of problem, it is time to redesign your website. You can improve your content with more interesting and useful articles or blog posts, include more images (because people prefer visuals rather than text) and also add some interactions on the website.</span>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style="color: #000000;">It''s not up-to-date</span></strong>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">The world of technology is one of the (if not THE) fastest changing industries. Which means that in just a few years or less some pretty cool stuff from today can be so old that no one remembers them . Keeping your website updated with the newest features and design trends is a guarantee for online marketing success. What''s more, the new technologies are made for better user experience so your outcome will be a satisfied customer.</span>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style="color: #000000;">It''s not easy to use</span></strong>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">If it happens that you are the one in charge of uploading content on your website, you might know that it could be hard for you to do it. But why is that? When today you have all the</span><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a style="color: #000000;" href="http://www.top10bestwebsitebuilders.com/WebsiteBuilders-Comparison?kw=professional%20web%20sites&amp;c=71889224917&amp;t=search&amp;p=&amp;m=p&amp;adpos=1t1&amp;dev=c&amp;devmod=&amp;mobval=0&amp;network=g&amp;campaignid=134707237&amp;adgroupid=7825402237&amp;targetid=kwd-101125489&amp;interest=&amp;physical=1005010&amp;feedid=&amp;a=2024&amp;ts=c&amp;topic=&amp;gclid=CjwKEAiArdG1BRCLvs_q-IObwxMSJACXbLtzHAhO0zlxY7-NHQi7FMDOdeokxJdbvndgT7fpKgHtMBoC6HXw_wcB"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> necessary tools to simplify the publishing process even if you are not a professional Web Designer. </span></a></span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The other side of not good usability is that your </span><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a style="color: #000000;" href="http://usabilitygeek.com/10-characteristics-bad-user-experience/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">user experience will be very bad</span></a></span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> and people will not be happy with what you give them online. Again why making it hard for your business to flourish when technology gives you the possibilities to rise and shine?</span></span>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style="color: #000000;">It''s not working properly</span></strong>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Oh, no... We all hate this, don''t we?  But sometimes when your website has not been updated recently, some of the features might stop working.And the visitors will be quite disappointed with that so you won''t get the results you''ve expected.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">This is why it is extremely important to check occasionally for the newest versions and update when possible. As George Bernard Shaw said:</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">"Progress is impossible without change." </span></i></span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Furthermore, don''t forget the increasing impact of </span><a style="color: #000000;" href="https://wearecrunchblog.wordpress.com/2016/02/04/6-things-you-should-do-when-promoting-your-business-in-social-media/"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">social media marketing</span> </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">and try to implement social buttons on visible places on your website.</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Last but not least, redesigning your website can be an amazing marketing strategy to win business over your competitors.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Let us know if there is any way we can help you!</span>', 'Do you need to redesign your business website now?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '259-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-04-13 09:52:13', '2016-04-13 09:52:13', '', 259, 'http://wearecrunch.net/newsite/2016/04/13/259-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(468, 1, '2016-04-13 09:55:01', '2016-04-13 09:55:01', '<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Facebook, twitter, LinkedIn, Instagram, Pinterest, Tumblr. There are so many social media platforms that you can easily get lost in the stream of information. And it sometimes seems so hard to choose that magical one which will bring you the tremendous success you are craving for.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">It''s easy to choose a social platform where you can share content related to your personal interests and hobbies. Typically, we prefer the ones that most of our friends and relatives use in order to easily connect with them.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">But when it comes to business, things can get tougher. Should we only care about our interests and favorite social media? The answer is no - not at all.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Because business is about other people’s needs and interests. These “other people” are our (potential) clients and they are the ones we work for.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Below, we''ve listed six things that will help you promote your business in social media.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Choose a proper platform</strong>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">When </span><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a style="color: #000000; text-decoration: underline;" href="http://www.entrepreneur.com/article/230020"><span style="font-weight: 400;">choosing a platform</span></a></span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"> t</span>he first thing you should take into consideration is your target audience. Your clients’ interests and preferences are most important because they will help you reveal what social media fits best your purpose.</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">The Internet is full of places where everyone can share thoughts and ideas and the best solution is to choose the one that reaches a bigger part of your target group. It is also crucial that you find the best fit for the type of media you would like to share. Both together are the ultimate combination for a social media triumph.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">In order to save you some time, we have shortly described what some of the social platforms are used for:</span>\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone wp-image-400 size-large" src="http://wearecrunch.net/newsite/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/social_media-1024x819.png" alt="social_media" width="900" height="720" />\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Depending on whether your company is B2B or B2C orientated and either you want to be presented mainly visually or not that much, you have plenty of possibilities to choose among. Reaching the target group can be done through each of the social platforms listed but the tone of voice should be set based on the purpose of the shared content.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Many companies use social media to build relationships with clients by sharing more personal and internal company information such as work in process, team brunch, etc.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Speak the language of your customers</strong>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">After you have conducted a research on your customers’ behaviour on social media, you should choose a tone of voice that responds to the one your target group is using. This will help you communicate with them in the finest way and, of course, will help you increase your sales.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Let us give you an example. You immediately get hungry hearing of the McMenu,right? And all of these Mc-Burgers that come to your mind when thinking of McDonald’s. mmm, yummy ...</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">This is due to the fact that they have established their own language and thought their customers how to use it.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">In fact, </span><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a style="color: #000000; text-decoration: underline;" href="https://stickybranding.com/how-to-speak-your-customers-language/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">speaking the client’s  language</span></a></span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> is practical for both social media promotion and any other kind of marketing strategy.</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">How to do it? Listen.Your customers have their own way of thinking when it comes to problem-solving and they have also gained personal experience. Get involved in conversations,find out what matters and give them what they need.</span>\r\n\r\n<strong>Be present</strong>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">It is a good habit to get used to using social media for your marketing purposes. And if you want to be noticed, you have to be active.Which means that you should update information on daily basis.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Go to your news feed and you will see that business pages that you have followed and have a good reputation in the market are quite active on their walls.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Let''s take Starbucks for example. Since the brand has joined Twitter is has more than 58,7k tweets. This makes 18+ tweets a day which is quite a lot. Still, people love it, they get involved in the conversations and actively re-tweet. Way to go, Starbucks!</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">But you should be careful not to be too annoying with posting every 10 minutes.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">In fact, we found a </span><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a style="color: #000000;" href="https://blog.bufferapp.com/how-often-post-social-media"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Buffer’s research</span></a></span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> saying that there are specific number of shared updates for each platform:</span></span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Social Media</span></td>\r\n<td><span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">How many times a DAY?</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Facebook</span></td>\r\n<td><span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">2</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">LinkedIn</span></td>\r\n<td><span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">1</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Instagram</span></td>\r\n<td><span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">1-3</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Google+</span></td>\r\n<td><span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">1,5+</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Pinterest</span></td>\r\n<td><span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">5+</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">twitter</span></td>\r\n<td><span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">3+</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Care about content</strong>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Being active in social media is wonderful when you have the creativity to come up with fascinating content.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">The Internet is so full of crap that most of the people are fed up with useless articles. You have to be extremely careful when choosing what to share (on the social media). People are quite judicious especially online. So find something captivating and worth reading to share with your followers. They will appreciate your effort to provide them with quality information.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">It is always a good idea to write something yourself and show that you are a professional so you may also consider </span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><a style="color: #000000;" href="http://blog.hubspot.com/marketing/the-benefits-of-business-blogging-ht">starting a blog.</a></span></span>\r\n\r\n<strong>Find the perfect moment</strong>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you </span><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a style="color: #000000;" href="http://www.entrepreneur.com/article/245515"><span style="font-weight: 400;">have the time resources</span></a></span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> to spend on making your own statistics when it is the perfect time to share, you are a lucky person.</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">And even if you find out that your targeted audience is visiting social media in a particular hour of day (for example at lunch time), probably there will be days when you are busy with something else - a non-planned meeting with client, you are about to fail with deadlines, or maybe your computer just crashed.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Relax. Fortunately, smart and ingenious people have invented tools like Buffer and Hootsuite which allow you to schedule posts and share them just in the perfect moment. What is more, they calculate the ideal time for sharing - the time when most people are online.</span>\r\n<h2></h2>\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">"Give and you shall receive." - Luke 6:38</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Considering that time is money, it’s a quite huge investment.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Your time is a treasure and we know it. It is pretty much of a challenge to devote yourself completely to social media. And you don’t need to do it. However, nowadays it is kind of crucial for your business to be presented online.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">In order not to mess it up, the proven solution is to make a social media marketing plan and follow it. Make it as simple as possible and don’t overthink it. Just set up goals and do the necessary to accomplish them.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Anyway, you know - good things take time.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">To sum up, social media is the modern way for developing a better marketing strategy.It’s easy and in the same time limitless.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Now it''s time for you to open the most creative part of your brain and start sharing!</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Let us know what is your own social media strategy in the comments below.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', '6 ways to improve your social media marketing results', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '222-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-04-13 09:55:01', '2016-04-13 09:55:01', '', 222, 'http://wearecrunch.net/newsite/2016/04/13/222-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(469, 1, '2016-04-13 09:57:08', '2016-04-13 09:57:08', '<span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">You have </span><a style="color: #000000;" href="https://wearecrunchblog.wordpress.com/2016/02/10/do-you-need-to-redesign-your-business-website-now/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">a well-designed company website</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> but somehow the results are not as good as you expected. Have you ever wondered what the reason might be? In a recent research, we''ve noticed some of the essential features for excellent website performance.</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Check if you haven''t missed to include one of the things we suggest in our list.</span>\r\n<h3><span style="color: #000000;"> </span></h3>\r\n<strong><span style="color: #000000;">Calls to action</span></strong>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">A call to action button (or CTA) is something that you should definitely include on your website.It is a useful tool for collecting information about people who are visiting your website and are interested in your products and services.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Either it''s a newsletter "subscribe" button or just a link to some related products or articles, it is one of the best ways to keep visitors on your website. Of course, these call-to-action buttons should lead to something worthwhile.</span>\r\n<h3><span style="color: #000000;"> </span></h3>\r\n<strong><span style="color: #000000;">Newsletter sign-up</span></strong>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Speaking of call-to-action buttons, it''s a great idea to have a newsletter sent occasionally to your clients who had subscribed.It''s basically the digital version of the free magazines and newspapers we can find in our mailboxes.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">First of all, think about the content of the newsletter and if you are able to provide your customers with valuable information, not just random ads of products.As you might guess, sending offers as a newsletter could increase sales but building a relationship with clients is a long-term return on investment.Show them that you care!</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">So make sure that your newsletter sign-up button is recognizable and attractive for the visitors and start creating appealing newsletters.</span>\r\n<h3><span style="color: #000000;"> </span></h3>\r\n<strong><span style="color: #000000;">Social media links</span></strong>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">For the time being, social media is a huge part of our everyday life and there is no doubt that it is a useful tool for deeper market penetration.Social media is a free channel through which you can reach a broader audience and easily communicate with customers.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Every successful business needs to be present on social media. However, an influential part of your social media strategy is including links to profiles on you company website.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Social media business profiles and pages can be incorporated into your website in different ways. You should, at least, have links to your various profiles on the template of your website. We will also recommend that content you provide is accompanied by a button for easy sharing.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;"><a style="color: #000000;" href="https://wearecrunchblog.wordpress.com/2016/02/04/6-things-you-should-do-when-promoting-your-business-in-social-media/">Learn more about Social Media here.</a></span>\r\n<h3><span style="color: #000000;"> </span></h3>\r\n<strong><span style="color: #000000;">Contact form</span></strong>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">First of all, providing your contact information on the template of your website could be crucial for your business. Depending on your choice of connecting people, you can include different channels - email address, phone number,store address, etc.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Secondly, technology has given us the opportunity to simplify things using contact forms directly on our website so customers have the possibility to quickly as a question and get the information they need.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Who wouldn''t want to do things in the easiest way possible? Why open thousands of new tabs when we can already send emails directly from the website we are on?  Only filling in several boxes and connection between you and your customer is established. Cool, no?</span>\r\n<h3><span style="color: #000000;"> </span></h3>\r\n<strong><span style="color: #000000;">Responsive design</span></strong>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Since browsing the Internet through mobile devices is becoming more and more common, you must consider optimizing your website for smartphones and tablets. "Responsive design" means that your website will look just as good on mobile devices as on desktop ones. And all of the features you''ve included won''t be missing or looking weird when viewed on smaller screen.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Furthermore, don''t forget to keep up-to-date with the latest trends because this is how you show respect to your customers - wanting to make them happy and satisfied with the experience on your website.</span>\r\n<h2><span style="color: #000000;"> </span></h2>\r\n<strong><span style="color: #000000;">Search engine optimization</span></strong>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Letting the search engines find your company website easily is crucial for your business, especially when you rely mainly on online marketing. Responsive design and social media presence are a big part of search engine optimization, yet there are many other ways to be on top of the results when potential customers are looking for you. It might be quite hard to do for non-professionals but there are a lot of competent companies who provide SEO service.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">So get to know the latest updates regarding SEO or trust someone who knows it to do it for you. Be present to be recognized.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">We hope that after going through this list, you will be aware of the necessary features for a great business website and it will help you improve your online marketing results.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">If you have any further questions or you want to share your experience with us, leave a comment below.</span>', '6 things your website is missing', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '410-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-04-13 09:57:08', '2016-04-13 09:57:08', '', 410, 'http://wearecrunch.net/newsite/2016/04/13/410-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
