(478, 1, '2016-04-13 10:50:48', '2016-04-13 10:50:48', '<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">If you are one of the people who still wonder if they should spend time and money on online marketing, we advise you to continue reading. It is becoming more and more popular for any kind and size of businesses to show up online. But you don’t have the extra budget to spend this year on something that you are not sure is going to work for you? Well, if you need some reasons to convince you, here are ours: </span>\n\n<span style="color: #000000;"><strong>An easy and fast way to reach more people </strong></span>\n\n<span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you are reading this, it means that you are one of the</span><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a style="color: #000000;" href="http://www.statista.com/statistics/273018/number-of-internet-users-worldwide/"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> 3,17 billion Internet users</span></a></span><span style="font-weight: 400;">. A huge number, isn’t it?  Of course, you won’t reach all of them but for sure you will expand your reach. Whether you are trying to reach youngsters or middle-aged, even our grandparents have access to the Web these days. </span></span>\n\n<span style="color: #000000;">Being visible online in the world of constant browsing can be crucial for your business. With your own website or blog, you will be able to show the World your products/services in a modern way and expand your reach.</span>\n\n<span style="color: #000000;">Social media is also a huge part of our everyday life. It gives you the opportunity to connect to and communicate with your customers and present yourself as a professional in your area of work.</span>\n\n<span style="color: #000000;"><strong>Cost effective </strong></span>\n\n<span style="color: #000000;">The budget is one of the most important parts of your business plan. When deciding whether or not to show up on the Internet, you might think that it could influence your budget in a negative way but consider this - the long term investment that you are making getting a company website will pay you back faster than you’ve imagined.</span>\n\n<span style="color: #000000;">There are also quite a few things you can do to promote our business online for free. For example, getting a Facebook or LinkedIn company page or sharing thoughts and pictures on twitter and Instagram. You can read more about your social media marketing opportunities here: (link to the other blog post)</span>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<span style="color: #000000;"><strong>Additional advertising and sales tool</strong></span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">In the virtual world, the size of your company does not really matter. With a good online marketing strategy, you can out rank in Google big international competitors. In fact, there are more small businesses that are still invisible online, so this might be a huge benefit for you to go ahead of the others and give your customers more. </span>\n\n<span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Consider also using social media to display for free your products or services. As </span><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a style="color: #000000; text-decoration: underline;" href="http://www.hubspot.com/company/management/brian-halligan"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Brian Halligan</span></a></span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> said</span><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">:” To be successful and grow your business and revenues, you must match the way you market your products with the way your prospects learn about and shop for your products.”</span></i></span>\n\n<span style="color: #000000;"><strong>Bigger impact </strong></span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">All good managers know that if you are following the latest trends, you are highly competitive and people are more likely to ask for your products or services. </span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="color: #000000;">Expanding your reach and establishing a good reputation online, gives you the opportunity to build better customer relationships and consequently attract new and bigger clients.</span> </span>', 'Why being present on the Internet is important for a business?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '460-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-04-13 10:50:48', '2016-04-13 10:50:48', '', 460, 'http://wearecrunch.net/newsite/2016/04/13/460-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
