(506, 1, '2016-04-20 10:09:18', '2016-04-20 10:09:18', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">The Chinese say “Show me and I will remember”. The way we approach life is through our eyes. From the very beginning of our life, we explore the world with our eyes. </span>\r\n\r\nOur memories consist mainly of pictures and sound - this is how we remember things. The impact of the visuals might turn out to be crucial when we are making particular decisions.\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">There is no doubt that some smart advertisers found out how to</span><a href="http://www.livescience.com/16169-advertisements-seduce-brain.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> “seduce” our brains </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">through imagery and make us buy their products or pay for the services they offer. There are for sure many tricks which can help when trying to promote your goods such as color, sound or an extraordinary way of storytelling.</span>\r\n\r\nIn many cases, people are unconsciously led by the way things look when making the decision which product to choose. This huge impact is due to the high levels of emotion that an image provokes.\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">According to a </span><a href="http://blog.hubspot.com/marketing/why-people-buy-factors-influence-purchase-descision"><span style="font-weight: 400;">HubSpot research</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">:</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">A visual search is one of the top 10 factors that influence purchase decisions. </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">44% of people on social media are most likely to engage with branded content that contains pictures.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">In case you want to get more customers through your company website, you need to consider a nice set of images.A good imagery could increase the </span><a href="https://moz.com/ugc/increasing-timeonpage-through-aesthetics-lessons-learned-from-prweb-and-buildzoom-two-large-content-sites"><span style="font-weight: 400;">time spent on the website</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> and eventually increase sales while </span><a href="http://blog.hubspot.com/marketing/compelling-stats-website-design-optimization-list"><span style="font-weight: 400;">38% of people will stop engaging with a website if the content/layout is unattractive.</span></a>\r\n\r\nAnd what could be better than a professional photographer with a high-resolution camera who also has the knowledge on editing pictures in a way that displays your goods in the finest way?\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">No matter what kind of business you are running, your chances of getting more trust and respectively new customers will become higher if you improve the quality of the images on your website. </span>\r\n\r\nThere are several ways you can get high-quality images - free stock photos, paid stock photos or professional photo session. It would be even better if you invest in buying a DSLR camera and learning how to use it but it might take time.\r\n\r\nSo, don’t underestimate the power of good imagery on your website. Find the most appropriate way for you (and your products/services) to stand out and start expanding your client reach.', 'Why professional photos are important for your website?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'why-professional-photos-are-important-for-your-business-website', '', '', '2016-04-20 10:18:55', '2016-04-20 10:18:55', '', 0, 'http://wearecrunch.net/newsite/?p=506', 0, 'post', '', 0),
