an><a href="https://moz.com/ugc/increasing-timeonpage-through-aesthetics-lessons-learned-from-prweb-and-buildzoom-two-large-content-sites"><span style="font-weight: 400;">time spent on the website</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> and eventually increase sales while </span><a href="http://blog.hubspot.com/marketing/compelling-stats-website-design-optimization-list"><span style="font-weight: 400;">38% of people will stop engaging with a website if the content/layout is unattractive.</span></a>\r\n\r\nAnd what could be better than a professional photographer with a high-resolution camera who also has the knowledge on editing pictures in a way that displays your goods in the finest way?\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">No matter what kind of business you are running, your chances of getting more trust and respectively new customers will become higher if you improve the quality of the images on your website. </span>\r\n\r\nThere are several ways you can get high-quality images - free stock photos, paid stock photos or professional photo session. It would be even better if you invest in buying a DSLR camera and learning how to use it but it might take time.\r\n\r\nSo, don’t underestimate the power of good imagery on your website. Find the most appropriate way for you (and your products/services) to stand out and start expanding your client reach.', 'Why professional photos are important for your business website?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '506-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-04-20 10:09:18', '2016-04-20 10:09:18', '', 506, 'http://wearecrunch.net/newsite/2016/04/20/506-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
